1

00:00:00,000  -->  00:00:02,680
System exit is an exception that Python

2

00:00:02,680  -->  00:00:06,000
raises when we want to stop the interpreter gracefully.

3

00:00:06,000  -->  00:00:08,880
Imagine you're closing the park at the end of the day.

4

00:00:08,880  -->  00:00:10,620
You're not dealing with a problem,

5

00:00:10,620  -->  00:00:13,200
just signaling that it's time to wrap things up.

6

00:00:13,200  -->  00:00:18,500
We don't often handle system exit because it's typically meant to be left alone,

7

00:00:18,500  -->  00:00:21,060
allowing Python to close smoothly.

8

00:00:21,060  -->  00:00:24,050
This will be a bit easier to see in an example.

9

00:00:24,050  -->  00:00:26,250
Let's dive into a demo.
